node.text:
Harmony is more achievable than balance. You can’t have every aspect of your life divided into equal parts (balance). With harmony, things ebb and flow together. 

#nedranuggets

node.title: The Difference Between Balance and Harmony

node.text:
ACT is a therapeutic modality is used with individuals and couples. The process is intended to help you become more of yourself by becoming more flexible in your thinking and being. 

Act Daily Journal by Dr. Diana Hill and Dr. Debbie Sorensen

node.text:
Watch this critical conversation with Dr. Karl Pillemer, the author of Fault Lines: Fractured Families and How to Mend Them.

In this conversation, we cover:
What is estrangement
How to reconcile
Keys times when people disconnect from family
How politics impact family relationships 
And more 

Shirt by @heytiffanyroe 

Guest @pillemer 

#nedranuggets 
#setboundariesfindpeace

node.text:
Sometimes we don't have an explanation for saying no, quilting, or not liking something. 

It's okay to trust your gut and do what's best for you.

Be assertive as a way to protect your mental health.

node.text:
People may not get it the first time. Give them time to adjust to your boundaries. If they aren't adjusting after some time (you determine the time frame), consider what needs to change about how you implemented the boundary.

Are you honoring your boundaries with others by holding them accountable? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Everything can't be resolved or fixed. You will have to leave some things without closure, take space without explaining or release them with love. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Leaving with your peace of mind intact is critical. 

Some situations will not allow you to end things gracefully. And you are not a terrible person for doing what you needed to be well. 

*This approach depends on the situation and does not apply as a go-to strategy.*

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6TYPES OF PEOPLE TO STAY CLOSETO @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Healthy relationships can (and do) change your life.

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6TYPES OF PEOPLE TO STAY CLOSETO @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who inspire you to be a better version of yourself. Don't be afraid to ask them questions about their journey. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who make you feel at ease. People who you can easily open up to and those who make you feel comfortable being vulnerable (asking, sharing, and receiving) are good for you. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who understand you. It's helpful to have relationships with people who have walked in your shoes. Also, it's meaningful to nurture relationships with people who are willing to learn even if your experiences are different. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who expose you to new things about yourself and the world. It's helpful to have a variety of friends. If everyone is just like you, you will have a hard time understanding anyone different from you. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who model healthy boundaries. Healthy behavio are contagious, and eventually, you might start to improve yourself by watching others operate in a healthy capacity. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.

Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stay close to people who challenge your thinking; this is not the same as people who make you question yourself. @nedratawwab www.nedratawwab.com'.
Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
I’m excited to announce that I’m a regular contributor on @facebook new platform Bulletin. 

Subscribe to my weekly newsletter available now on Bulletin. 

In my weekly newsletter (Nedra Nuggets), I am digging deeper into topics on mental health and relationships. My first two articles are posted, and I’m excited to see your comments.

www.nedratawwab.bulletin.com

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 20, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Sometimes the choice is you or them. I hope you choose yourself because you are the only person you can please most of the time. 

Choosing yourself is a thoughtful way to make yourself proud. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Let's practice going to therapy with the intention of wellness, not just when you're in crisis. Therapy is a space to learn more about yourself, your relationships, and how your life experiences impact you. You can go to therapy without having a major life problem and with the intention of growth, remaining productive, and just to talk to a neutral party. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Therapists are there to listen to you talk about your problems, help you navigate finding solutions, guide you through your feelings and hold space for you. 

Normalize therapy as a preventive strategy, not just as a solution to a crisis. 

#nedranuggets

Restorative Reading 

• Their Eyes Were Watching God by Zora Neale Hurston
• What I Know For Sure by Oprah
• All Along You Were Blooming by 
• Morgan Harper Nichols 
After The Rain by Alex Elle
• The Unapologetic Guide to Black Mental Health by Rheeda Walker PhD 
• Sisters of the Yam by bell hooks 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 17, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'As I mature, the less I want to: @NEDRATAWWAB Have shallow connections Judge others for making mistakes that I've made too Gossip about others to feel good about myself Minimize my accomplishments Do everything on my own (I'm okay with asking for help) Listen to everyone's opinion Put energy into unhealthy relationships Tell people what they want to hear instead of the truth WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
As you mature, your focus will shift. 

Maturity is not based on age; it's a change in mindset. 

What shifts have you noticed within yourself? 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
Just because someone isn't good for you doesn't mean that they're a terrible person.

We can disconnect from people and acknowledge the good parts of the relationship. It's healthy to remember both. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'You can move on and... @NEDRATAWWAB still be sad reminisce wish things were different hope things will chang still love someone still care deeply wonder what if heal while in another relationship have regrets WW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
It's a process...

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A little secret from a therapist: Sometimes being a provider is not seen as love when what a person needed was presence. When you take the time to learn and reflect what people need to feel loved, they will feel loved. Doing what you think is loving may not be enough for someone who is looking for a particular type of love. Practice getting to know people and uniquely loving them. Repeat After Me: I'm unique, therefore what I need from others is unique. @NEDRATAWWAB WWW.NEDRATAWWAB.COM'.

node.text:
Let people know how to love you. 

Sometimes you need presence.
Sometimes you need kind words.
Sometimes you need someone to listen to you.

You needs are unique.

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'If You Want to Grow, Stop Doing This: @NEDRATAWWAB Looking for perfection in other people Giving advice that you don't apply to yourself Discounting other viewpoints Deciding that you're damaged/broken Ruling out the possibility that things can go well Assuming that your way is best (be open) Putting people down as a way to build yourself up Comparing yourself to people who aren't competing with you Always observing what someone did to you without noticing how you contributed to the situation www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
Stop doing things that get in the way of your growth. 

#nedranuggets

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nedra Glover Tawwab, Therapist on July 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Things That We Outgrow @NEDRATAWWAB Relationships Ways of thinking Our Old Self Hair Styles Preferences Habits/ Habits/Behaviors Clothes Shoes Anything that no longer fits who we are www.nedratawwab.com'.

node.text:
You’ve been outgrowing things your entire life, and today is no different.

You will not always be the same person. It's normal to change and to be a different version of yourself. Hopefully, you keep what you need and release the things that no longer fit. 

#nedranuggets
